Sentece: In a radioligand binding assay, DiPOA inhibited [(3)H]-diprenorphine binding to recombinant human mu receptors with a K(i) value of approximately 0.8 nM.
Title: DiPOA ([8-(3,3-diphenyl-propyl)-4-oxo-1-phenyl-1,3,8-triazaspiro[4.5]dec-3-yl]-acetic acid), a novel, systemically available, and peripherally restricted mu opioid agonist with antihyperalgesic activity: I. In vitro pharmacological characterization and pharmacokinetic properties.
Name: Diprenorphine

Sentece: DiPOA showed potent agonist effects in a human mu receptor guanosine 5'-O-(3-[(35)S]thio)triphosphate functional assay, with an EC(50) value of approximately 33 nM and efficacy of approximately 85% [normalized to the mu agonist, [d-Ala2,MePhe4,Gly(ol)5]enkephalin].
Title: DiPOA ([8-(3,3-diphenyl-propyl)-4-oxo-1-phenyl-1,3,8-triazaspiro[4.5]dec-3-yl]-acetic acid), a novel, systemically available, and peripherally restricted mu opioid agonist with antihyperalgesic activity: I. In vitro pharmacological characterization and pharmacokinetic properties.
Name: Diprenorphine

Sentece: High and sustained (> or =5 h) plasma levels for DiPOA were achieved following intraperitoneal administration at 3 and 10 mg/kg; central nervous system penetration, however, was < or =4% of the plasma concentration, even at levels exceeding 1500 ng/ml.
Title: DiPOA ([8-(3,3-diphenyl-propyl)-4-oxo-1-phenyl-1,3,8-triazaspiro[4.5]dec-3-yl]-acetic acid), a novel, systemically available, and peripherally restricted mu opioid agonist with antihyperalgesic activity: I. In vitro pharmacological characterization and pharmacokinetic properties.
Name: Diprenorphine
